06/03/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The armies of Macedonia and Albania will conduct a joint military drill this month at Macedonia's Krivolak military base. 
The decision was reached during a meeting Wednesday (5 March) between Macedonian Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski and Albanian Defence Ministry official Brig Gen Luan Hoxha. 
They also planned a second a joint alpine training exercise, with the support of the Swiss Defence Ministry, for the second half of this year and discussed efforts to strengthen regional security. 
(MIA, Makfax - 05/03/03)
